{"parentUuid":"b7919192-e89b-47c0-ba99-bb5a447cd108","isSidechain":false,"userType":"external","cwd":"C:\\Users\\ColsonR\\apstats-live-worksheet","sessionId":"a26dd791-6ed3-408b-a594-2da0ac778535","version":"2.1.69","gitBranch":"master","slug":"twinkling-giggling-barto","type":"progress","data":{"type":"hook_progress","hookEvent":"PostToolUse","hookName":"PostToolUse:Read","command":"callback"},"parentToolUseID":"toolu_01ApNL5KgHGaNtc8AQ8VuvDP","toolUseID":"toolu_01ApNL5KgHGaNtc8AQ8VuvDP","timestamp":"2026-03-05T02:44:50.268Z","uuid":"ca50ae3f-0054-4c20-88cf-3f9efad09102"}
{"parentUuid":"b7919192-e89b-47c0-ba99-bb5a447cd108","isSidechain":false,"userType":"external","cwd":"C:\\Users\\ColsonR\\apstats-live-worksheet","sessionId":"a26dd791-6ed3-408b-a594-2da0ac778535","version":"2.1.69","gitBranch":"master","slug":"twinkling-giggling-barto","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01ApNL5KgHGaNtc8AQ8VuvDP","type":"tool_result","content":"   600→            <span class=\"question-number\">R1.</span>\n   601→            <strong>The sample mean of {0, 2, 5} was 2.3 &mdash; way off from the population mean of 5. Yet we still call <span style=\"text-decoration: overline;\">x</span> an \"unbiased\" estimator. Explain what \"unbiased\" actually promises and what it does <em>not</em> promise about any single sample.</strong>\n   602→            <textarea id=\"reflect1\" placeholder=\"Write your response here...\"></textarea>\n   603→            <div id=\"reflect1-feedback\"></div>\n   604→        </div>\n   605→\n   606→        <div class=\"question\">\n   607→            <span class=\"question-number\">R2.</span>\n   608→            <strong>Explain in your own words why the sample range is a biased estimator of the population range. Use the Weimaraner example to describe <em>why</em> the bias goes in one direction (always underestimating, never overestimating). Could a different statistic be biased in the opposite direction &mdash; systematically overestimating?</strong>\n   609→            <textarea id=\"reflect2\" placeholder=\"Write your response here...\"></textarea>\n   610→            <div id=\"reflect2-feedback\"></div>\n   611→        </div>\n   612→    </div>\n   613→\n   614→    <!-- ============================================================ -->\n   615→    <!-- EXIT TICKET                                                   -->\n   616→    <!-- ============================================================ -->\n   617→    <div class=\"exit-ticket\">\n   618→        <h3 style=\"margin-top: 0; color: #003366;\">Exit Ticket</h3>\n   619→        <div class=\"question\">\n   620→            <strong>A population of 4 students has quiz scores: {60, 70, 80, 90}. The population mean is 75 and the population range is 30. A researcher takes all possible samples of size 2.</strong>\n   621→            <ul style=\"margin: 8px 0;\">\n   622→                <li>(a) Would you expect the mean of all sample means to equal 75? Explain why, using what you learned about bias.</li>\n   623→                <li>(b) Would you expect the mean of all sample ranges to equal 30? Why or why not?</li>\n   624→                <li>(c) Based on your answers, which statistic &mdash; sample mean or sample range &mdash; is a more trustworthy estimator of its corresponding parameter? Explain.</li>\n   625→            </ul>\n   626→            <textarea id=\"exitTicket\" placeholder=\"Show your reasoning for each part...\"></textarea>\n   627→            <div id=\"exitTicket-feedback\"></div>\n   628→        </div>\n   629→    </div>\n   630→\n   631→    <!-- Aggregate Drawer -->\n   632→    <div id=\"aggregateDrawer\" class=\"aggregate-drawer\">\n   633→        <div class=\"drawer-header\">\n   634→            <h3>Class Responses <span style=\"font-size: 0.7em; color: #999; font-weight: normal;\">(Esc to close)</span></h3>\n   635→            <button class=\"drawer-close\" onclick=\"closeDrawer()\">&times;</button>\n   636→        </div>\n   637→        <div class=\"drawer-content\" id=\"drawerContent\">\n   638→            <p>Click a \"Class\" button next to a question to see responses.</p>\n   639→        </div>\n   640→    </div>\n   641→\n   642→    <!-- Scripts -->\n   643→    <script src=\"../railway_config.js\"></script>\n   644→    <script src=\"../railway_client.js\"></script>\n   645→    <script src=\"ai-grading-prompts-u5-l4.js\"></script>\n   646→    <script>\n   647→        // ==================== CONFIG ====================\n   648→        const UNIT_ID = 'U5L4';\n   649→        const DEBOUNCE_MS = 250;\n   650→\n   651→        // ==================== STATE ====================\n   652→        let debounceMap = new Map();\n   653→        let currentQuestionBlanks = [];\n   654→        let gradingState = new Map();\n   655→\n   656→        // ==================== INIT ====================\n   657→        document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', init);\n   658→\n   659→        function init() {\n   660→            ensureRailwayDefaults();\n   661→            restoreSavedUser();\n   662→            assignQuestionIds();\n   663→            addSaveIndicators();\n   664→            bindBlankEvents();\n   665→            injectAggregateButtons();\n   666→        }\n   667→\n   668→        function ensureRailwayDefaults() {\n   669→            if (!window.RAILWAY_SERVER_URL) {\n   670→                window.RAILWAY_SERVER_URL = 'https://curriculumrender-production.up.railway.app';\n   671→            }\n   672→        }\n   673→\n   674→        // ==================== USER PERSISTENCE ====================\n   675→        function restoreSavedUser() {\n   676→            try {\n   677→                const saved = localStorage.getItem('worksheet-user');\n   678→                if (saved) {\n   679→                    const user = JSON.parse(saved);\n   680→                    if (user.name) document.getElementById('worksheetName').value = user.name;\n   681→                    if (user.klass) document.getElementById('worksheetPeriod').value = user.klass;\n   682→                    if (user.username) document.getElementById('worksheetUsername').value = user.username;\n   683→                }\n   684→            } catch (e) { console.warn('Could not restore user', e); }\n   685→        }\n   686→\n   687→        function saveUser() {\n   688→            const user = {\n   689→                name: document.getElementById('worksheetName').value,\n   690→                klass: document.getElementById('worksheetPeriod').value,\n   691→                username: document.getElementById('worksheetUsername').value\n   692→            };\n   693→            localStorage.setItem('worksheet-user', JSON.stringify(user));\n   694→        }\n   695→\n   696→        function getUsername() {\n   697→            return (document.getElementById('worksheetUsername').value || '').trim();\n   698→        }\n   699→\n   700→        document.getElementById('worksheetUsername').addEventListener('blur', saveUser);\n   701→        document.getElementById('worksheetName').addEventListener('blur', saveUser);\n   702→        document.getElementById('worksheetPeriod').addEventListener('blur', saveUser);\n   703→\n   704→        // ==================== QUESTION IDs & EVENTS ====================\n   705→        function assignQuestionIds() {\n   706→            const blanks = document.querySelectorAll('.blank');\n   707→            blanks.forEach((blank, idx) => {\n   708→                blank.dataset.questionId = `WS-${UNIT_ID}-Q${idx + 1}`;\n   709→            });\n   710→        }\n   711→\n   712→        function addSaveIndicators() {\n   713→            document.querySelectorAll('.question').forEach(q => {\n   714→                if (!q.querySelector('.save-indicator')) {\n   715→                    const indicator = document.createElement('span');\n   716→                    indicator.className = 'save-indicator';\n   717→                    indicator.textContent = '\\u2713 saved';\n   718→                    q.appendChild(indicator);\n   719→                }\n   720→            });\n   721→        }\n   722→\n   723→        function bindBlankEvents() {\n   724→            document.querySelectorAll('.blank').forEach(blank => {\n   725→                blank.addEventListener('blur', () => handleLiveUpdate(blank));\n   726→                blank.addEventListener('keydown', (e) => {\n   727→                    if (e.key === 'Enter') {\n   728→                        e.preventDefault();\n   729→                        handleLiveUpdate(blank);\n   730→                        focusNextBlank(blank);\n   731→                    }\n   732→                });\n   733→            });\n   734→        }\n   735→\n   736→        function focusNextBlank(current) {\n   737→            const blanks = Array.from(document.querySelectorAll('.blank'));\n   738→            const idx = blanks.indexOf(current);\n   739→            if (idx >= 0 && idx < blanks.length - 1) {\n   740→                blanks[idx + 1].focus();\n   741→            }\n   742→        }\n   743→\n   744→        // ==================== ANSWER CHECKING ====================\n   745→        function normalize(str) {\n   746→            return (str || '').toLowerCase().trim().replace(/[^\\w\\s./-]/g, '');\n   747→        }\n   748→\n   749→        function checkAnswer(blank) {\n   750→            const userAnswer = normalize(blank.value);\n   751→            const acceptedRaw = blank.dataset.answer || '';\n   752→            const accepted = acceptedRaw.split('|').map(normalize);\n   753→\n   754→            blank.classList.remove('correct', 'partial', 'incorrect', 'revealed');\n   755→\n   756→            if (!userAnswer) return 'empty';\n   757→\n   758→            if (accepted.includes(userAnswer)) {\n   759→                blank.classList.add('correct');\n   760→                return 'correct';\n   761→            }\n   762→\n   763→            const partialMatch = accepted.some(ans =>\n   764→                userAnswer.includes(ans) || ans.includes(userAnswer)\n   765→            );\n   766→            if (partialMatch) {\n   767→                blank.classList.add('partial');\n   768→                return 'partial';\n   769→            }\n   770→\n   771→            blank.classList.add('incorrect');\n   772→            return 'incorrect';\n   773→        }\n   774→\n   775→        function checkAnswers() {\n   776→            const blanks = document.querySelectorAll('.blank');\n   777→            let correct = 0, partial = 0, total = 0;\n   778→\n   779→            blanks.forEach(blank => {\n   780→                if (blank.value.trim()) {\n   781→                    total++;\n   782→                    const result = checkAnswer(blank);\n   783→                    if (result === 'correct') correct++;\n   784→                    else if (result === 'partial') partial++;\n   785→                }\n   786→            });\n   787→\n   788→            const scoreEl = document.getElementById('scoreDisplay');\n   789→            if (total > 0) {\n   790→                const pct = Math.round((correct / total) * 100);\n   791→                scoreEl.textContent = `Score: ${correct}/${total} (${pct}%)` + (partial > 0 ? ` +${partial} partial` : '');\n   792→                scoreEl.classList.add('visible');\n   793→            } else {\n   794→                scoreEl.classList.remove('visible');\n   795→            }\n   796→\n   797→            pushAllAnswers();\n   798→            refreshDrawerIfOpen();\n   799→        }\n   800→\n   801→        function showAnswers() {\n   802→            document.querySelectorAll('.blank').forEach(blank => {\n   803→                const answers = (blank.dataset.answer || '').split('|');\n   804→                blank.value = answers[0] || '';\n   805→                blank.classList.remove('correct', 'partial', 'incorrect');\n   806→                blank.classList.add('revealed');\n   807→            });\n   808→            document.getElementById('scoreDisplay').classList.remove('visible');\n   809→            pushAllAnswers();\n   810→            refreshDrawerIfOpen();\n   811→        }\n   812→\n   813→        function resetAnswers() {\n   814→            document.querySelectorAll('.blank').forEach(blank => {\n   815→                blank.value = '';\n   816→                blank.classList.remove('correct', 'partial', 'incorrect', 'revealed');\n   817→            });\n   818→            document.querySelectorAll('textarea').forEach(ta => {\n   819→                ta.value = '';\n   820→                ta.classList.remove('graded-E', 'graded-P', 'graded-I');\n   821→            });\n   822→            document.querySelectorAll('.ai-feedback').forEach(fb => fb.remove());\n   823→            document.getElementById('scoreDisplay').classList.remove('visible');\n   824→            gradingState.clear();\n   825→        }\n   826→\n   827→        // ==================== SERVER SYNC ====================\n   828→        function handleLiveUpdate(blank) {\n   829→            const questionId = blank.dataset.questionId;\n   830→            if (!questionId) return;\n   831→\n   832→            const now = Date.now();\n   833→            const lastTime = debounceMap.get(questionId) || 0;\n   834→            if (now - lastTime < DEBOUNCE_MS) return;\n   835→            debounceMap.set(questionId, now);\n   836→\n   837→            sendAnswer(blank);\n   838→        }\n   839→\n   840→        async function sendAnswer(blank) {\n   841→            const username = getUsername();\n   842→            if (!username) return;\n   843→\n   844→            const questionId = blank.dataset.questionId;\n   845→            const answer = blank.value.trim();\n   846→\n   847→            try {\n   848→                if (window.railwayClient && window.railwayClient.submitAnswer) {\n   849→                    await window.railwayClient.submitAnswer(username, questionId, answer);\n   850→                } else {\n   851→                    await fetch(`${window.RAILWAY_SERVER_URL}/api/submit-answer`, {\n   852→                        method: 'POST',\n   853→                        headers: { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' },\n   854→                        body: JSON.stringify({\n   855→                            username,\n   856→                            question_id: questionId,\n   857→                            answer_value: answer,\n   858→                            timestamp: Date.now()\n   859→                        })\n   860→                    });\n   861→                }\n   862→                showSaved(blank);\n   863→                spawnUploadParticle(blank);\n   864→            } catch (err) {\n   865→                console.warn('Failed to sync answer:', err);\n   866→            }\n   867→        }\n   868→\n   869→        function pushAllAnswers() {\n   870→            document.querySelectorAll('.blank').forEach(blank => {\n   871→                if (blank.value.trim()) sendAnswer(blank);\n   872→            });\n   873→        }\n   874→\n   875→        function showSaved(blank) {\n   876→            const question = blank.closest('.question');\n   877→            if (!question) return;\n   878→            const indicator = question.querySelector('.save-indicator');\n   879→            if (indicator) {\n   880→                indicator.classList.add('visible');\n   881→                setTimeout(() => indicator.classList.remove('visible'), 2000);\n   882→            }\n   883→        }\n   884→\n   885→        function spawnUploadParticle(blank) {\n   886→            const particle = document.createElement('span');\n   887→            particle.className = 'upload-particle';\n   888→            particle.textContent = '\\u2191';\n   889→            const rect = blank.getBoundingClientRect();\n   890→            particle.style.left = `${rect.left + rect.width / 2}px`;\n   891→            particle.style.top = `${rect.top - 5}px`;\n   892→            particle.style.position = 'fixed';\n   893→            document.body.appendChild(particle);\n   894→            setTimeout(() => particle.remove(), 900);\n   895→        }\n   896→\n   897→        // ==================== AGGREGATE DRAWER ====================\n   898→        function injectAggregateButtons() {\n   899→            document.querySelectorAll('.question').forEach(q => {\n   900→                const blanks = q.querySelectorAll('.blank');\n   901→                if (blanks.length > 0 && !q.querySelector('.aggregate-trigger')) {\n   902→                    const btn = document.createElement('button');\n   903→                    btn.className = 'aggregate-trigger';\n   904→                    btn.textContent = '\\uD83D\\uDCCA Class';\n   905→                    btn.onclick = () => openDrawerForQuestion(q);\n   906→                    q.appendChild(btn);\n   907→                }\n   908→            });\n   909→        }\n   910→\n   911→        function openDrawerForQuestion(questionEl) {\n   912→            currentQuestionBlanks = Array.from(questionEl.querySelectorAll('.blank'));\n   913→            const drawer = document.getElementById('aggregateDrawer');\n   914→            const content = document.getElementById('drawerContent');\n   915→\n   916→            drawer.classList.add('open');\n   917→            content.innerHTML = '<p>Loading...</p>';\n   918→\n   919→            loadAggregateData();\n   920→        }\n   921→\n   922→        async function loadAggregateData() {\n   923→            const content = document.getElementById('drawerContent');\n   924→            let html = '';\n   925→\n   926→            for (const blank of currentQuestionBlanks) {\n   927→                const questionId = blank.dataset.questionId;\n   928→                if (!questionId) continue;\n   929→\n   930→                try {\n   931→                    const stats = await fetchQuestionStats(questionId);\n   932→                    html += renderBarChart(questionId, stats);\n   933→                } catch (err) {\n   934→                    html += `<p>Error loading ${questionId}</p>`;\n   935→                }\n   936→            }\n   937→\n   938→            content.innerHTML = html || '<p>No data available.</p>';\n   939→            spawnPeerSnow();\n   940→        }\n   941→\n   942→        async function fetchQuestionStats(questionId) {\n   943→            if (window.railwayClient && window.railwayClient.getStats) {\n   944→                return await window.railwayClient.getStats(questionId);\n   945→            }\n   946→            const res = await fetch(`${window.RAILWAY_SERVER_URL}/api/question-stats/${questionId}`);\n   947→            return await res.json();\n   948→        }\n   949→\n   950→        function renderBarChart(questionId, stats) {\n   951→            const responses = stats.responses || stats.distribution || {};\n   952→            const entries = Object.entries(responses).sort((a, b) => b[1] - a[1]);\n   953→            const maxCount = entries.length > 0 ? Math.max(...entries.map(([, c]) => c)) : 0;\n   954→\n   955→            if (entries.length === 0) {\n   956→                return `<div class=\"bar-chart\"><strong>${questionId}</strong><p>No responses yet</p></div>`;\n   957→            }\n   958→\n   959→            let html = `<div class=\"bar-chart\"><strong>${questionId}</strong>`;\n   960→            entries.slice(0, 8).forEach(([answer, count]) => {\n   961→                const widthPct = maxCount > 0 ? (count / maxCount) * 100 : 0;\n   962→                html += `\n   963→                    <div class=\"bar-row\">\n   964→                        <span class=\"bar-label\" title=\"${answer}\">${answer}</span>\n   965→                        <div class=\"bar-container\">\n   966→                            <div class=\"bar-fill\" style=\"width: ${widthPct}%\"></div>\n   967→                        </div>\n   968→                        <span class=\"bar-count\">${count}</span>\n   969→                    </div>\n   970→                `;\n   971→            });\n   972→            html += '</div>';\n   973→            return html;\n   974→        }\n   975→\n   976→        function closeDrawer() {\n   977→            document.getElementById('aggregateDrawer').classList.remove('open');\n   978→            currentQuestionBlanks = [];\n   979→        }\n   980→\n   981→        // Escape key closes drawer\n   982→        document.addEventListener('keydown', (e) => {\n   983→            if (e.key === 'Escape' && document.getElementById('aggregateDrawer').classList.contains('open')) {\n   984→                closeDrawer();\n   985→            }\n   986→        });\n   987→\n   988→        function refreshDrawerIfOpen() {\n   989→            if (document.getElementById('aggregateDrawer').classList.contains('open') && currentQuestionBlanks.length > 0) {\n   990→                loadAggregateData();\n   991→            }\n   992→        }\n   993→\n   994→        function spawnPeerSnow() {\n   995→            for (let i = 0; i < 5; i++) {\n   996→                setTimeout(() => {\n   997→                    const snow = document.createElement('span');\n   998→                    snow.textContent = '\\u2744';\n   999→                    snow.style.cssText = `\n  1000→                        position: fixed;\n  1001→                        right: ${20 + Math.random() * 300}px;\n  1002→                        top: ${100 + Math.random() * 200}px;\n  1003→                        font-size: 1.2em;\n  1004→                        color: #90caf9;\n  1005→                        pointer-events: none;\n  1006→                        animation: snowDrift 1.4s ease-out forwards;\n  1007→                    `;\n  1008→                    document.body.appendChild(snow);\n  1009→                    setTimeout(() => snow.remove(), 1400);\n  1010→                }, i * 100);\n  1011→            }\n  1012→        }\n  1013→\n  1014→        // ==================== AI GRADING ====================\n  1015→        async function gradeAllReflections() {\n  1016→            const btn = document.querySelector('.btn-ai');\n  1017→            btn.disabled = true;\n  1018→            btn.textContent = '\\u23F3 Grading...';\n  1019→\n  1020→            const textareas = ['reflect1', 'reflect2', 'exitTicket'];\n  1021→\n  1022→            for (const id of textareas) {\n  1023→                const textarea = document.getElementById(id);\n  1024→                if (!textarea) continue;\n  1025→\n  1026→                const answer = textarea.value.trim();\n  1027→                if (answer.length < 20) {\n  1028→                    showFeedback(id, { score: 'I', feedback: 'Please write a more complete response (at least 20 characters).' });\n  1029→                    continue;\n  1030→                }\n  1031→\n  1032→                try {\n  1033→                    const result = await gradeReflection(id, answer);\n  1034→                    gradingState.set(id, {\n  1035→                        result,\n  1036→                        originalAnswer: answer,\n  1037→                        appealCount: 0,\n  1038→                        history: []\n  1039→                    });\n  1040→                    showFeedback(id, result);\n  1041→                } catch (err) {\n  1042→                    console.error('Grading error:', err);\n  1043→                    showFeedback(id, { score: 'I', feedback: 'Error grading response. Please try again.' });\n  1044→                }\n  1045→            }\n  1046→\n  1047→            btn.disabled = false;\n  1048→            btn.textContent = '\\uD83E\\uDD16 Grade My Reflections';\n  1049→        }\n  1050→\n  1051→        async function gradeReflection(questionId, answer) {\n  1052→            if (!window.buildReflectionPromptU5L4) {\n  1053→                throw new Error('AI grading prompts not loaded');\n  1054→            }\n  1055→\n  1056→            const prompt = window.buildReflectionPromptU5L4(questionId, answer);\n  1057→            const rubric = window.getRubricU5L4(questionId);\n  1058→\n  1059→            const response = await fetch(`${window.RAILWAY_SERVER_URL}/api/ai/grade`, {\n  1060→                method: 'POST',\n  1061→                headers: { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' },\n  1062→                body: JSON.stringify({\n  1063→                    scenario: {\n  1064→                        topic: 'AP Statistics - Biased and Unbiased Point Estimates',\n  1065→                        questionId,\n  1066→                        lessonContext: window.LESSON_CONTEXT_U5L4\n  1067→                    },\n  1068→                    answers: { answer },\n  1069→                    prompt\n  1070→                })\n  1071→            });\n  1072→\n  1073→            if (!response.ok) throw new Error('Grading request failed');\n  1074→            return await response.json();\n  1075→        }\n  1076→\n  1077→        function showFeedback(questionId, result) {\n  1078→            const textarea = document.getElementById(questionId);\n  1079→            if (!textarea) return;\n  1080→\n  1081→            textarea.classList.remove('graded-E', 'graded-P', 'graded-I');\n  1082→            textarea.classList.add(`graded-${result.score}`);\n  1083→\n  1084→            const container = document.getElementById(`${questionId}-feedback`);\n  1085→            container.innerHTML = '';\n  1086→\n  1087→            const feedback = document.createElement('div');\n  1088→            feedback.className = 'ai-feedback';\n  1089→\n  1090→            let html = `\n  1091→                <div class=\"ai-feedback-header\">\n  1092→                    <span class=\"score-badge score-${result.score}\">${result.score === 'E' ? 'Essentially Correct' : result.score === 'P' ? 'Partially Correct' : 'Incorrect'}</span>\n  1093→                </div>\n  1094→                <div class=\"ai-feedback-body\">${result.feedback || ''}</div>\n  1095→            `;\n  1096→\n  1097→            if (result.matched && result.matched.length > 0) {\n  1098→                html += `<div class=\"ai-feedback-matched\">\\u2713 You addressed: ${result.matched.join(', ')}</div>`;\n  1099→            }"}]},"uuid":"9ec4ca9d-c60c-4ea4-ae55-2336400889ef","timestamp":"2026-03-05T02:44:50.268Z","toolUseResult":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"C:\\Users\\ColsonR\\apstats-live-worksheet\\u5_lesson4_live.html","content":"            <span class=\"question-number\">R1.</span>\n            <strong>The sample mean of {0, 2, 5} was 2.3 &mdash; way off from the population mean of 5. Yet we still call <span style=\"text-decoration: overline;\">x</span> an \"unbiased\" estimator. Explain what \"unbiased\" actually promises and what it does <em>not</em> promise about any single sample.</strong>\n            <textarea id=\"reflect1\" placeholder=\"Write your response here...\"></textarea>\n            <div id=\"reflect1-feedback\"></div>\n        </div>\n\n        <div class=\"question\">\n            <span class=\"question-number\">R2.</span>\n            <strong>Explain in your own words why the sample range is a biased estimator of the population range. Use the Weimaraner example to describe <em>why</em> the bias goes in one direction (always underestimating, never overestimating). Could a different statistic be biased in the opposite direction &mdash; systematically overestimating?</strong>\n            <textarea id=\"reflect2\" placeholder=\"Write your response here...\"></textarea>\n            <div id=\"reflect2-feedback\"></div>\n        </div>\n    </div>\n\n    <!-- ============================================================ -->\n    <!-- EXIT TICKET                                                   -->\n    <!-- ============================================================ -->\n    <div class=\"exit-ticket\">\n        <h3 style=\"margin-top: 0; color: #003366;\">Exit Ticket</h3>\n        <div class=\"question\">\n            <strong>A population of 4 students has quiz scores: {60, 70, 80, 90}. The population mean is 75 and the population range is 30. A researcher takes all possible samples of size 2.</strong>\n            <ul style=\"margin: 8px 0;\">\n                <li>(a) Would you expect the mean of all sample means to equal 75? Explain why, using what you learned about bias.</li>\n                <li>(b) Would you expect the mean of all sample ranges to equal 30? Why or why not?</li>\n                <li>(c) Based on your answers, which statistic &mdash; sample mean or sample range &mdash; is a more trustworthy estimator of its corresponding parameter? Explain.</li>\n            </ul>\n            <textarea id=\"exitTicket\" placeholder=\"Show your reasoning for each part...\"></textarea>\n            <div id=\"exitTicket-feedback\"></div>\n        </div>\n    </div>\n\n    <!-- Aggregate Drawer -->\n    <div id=\"aggregateDrawer\" class=\"aggregate-drawer\">\n        <div class=\"drawer-header\">\n            <h3>Class Responses <span style=\"font-size: 0.7em; color: #999; font-weight: normal;\">(Esc to close)</span></h3>\n            <button class=\"drawer-close\" onclick=\"closeDrawer()\">&times;</button>\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"drawer-content\" id=\"drawerContent\">\n            <p>Click a \"Class\" button next to a question to see responses.</p>\n        </div>\n    </div>\n\n    <!-- Scripts -->\n    <script src=\"../railway_config.js\"></script>\n    <script src=\"../railway_client.js\"></script>\n    <script src=\"ai-grading-prompts-u5-l4.js\"></script>\n    <script>\n        // ==================== CONFIG ====================\n        const UNIT_ID = 'U5L4';\n        const DEBOUNCE_MS = 250;\n\n        // ==================== STATE ====================\n        let debounceMap = new Map();\n        let currentQuestionBlanks = [];\n        let gradingState = new Map();\n\n        // ==================== INIT ====================\n        document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', init);\n\n        function init() {\n            ensureRailwayDefaults();\n            restoreSavedUser();\n            assignQuestionIds();\n            addSaveIndicators();\n            bindBlankEvents();\n            injectAggregateButtons();\n        }\n\n        function ensureRailwayDefaults() {\n            if (!window.RAILWAY_SERVER_URL) {\n                window.RAILWAY_SERVER_URL = 'https://curriculumrender-production.up.railway.app';\n            }\n        }\n\n        // ==================== USER PERSISTENCE ====================\n        function restoreSavedUser() {\n            try {\n                const saved = localStorage.getItem('worksheet-user');\n                if (saved) {\n                    const user = JSON.parse(saved);\n                    if (user.name) document.getElementById('worksheetName').value = user.name;\n                    if (user.klass) document.getElementById('worksheetPeriod').value = user.klass;\n                    if (user.username) document.getElementById('worksheetUsername').value = user.username;\n                }\n            } catch (e) { console.warn('Could not restore user', e); }\n        }\n\n        function saveUser() {\n            const user = {\n                name: document.getElementById('worksheetName').value,\n                klass: document.getElementById('worksheetPeriod').value,\n                username: document.getElementById('worksheetUsername').value\n            };\n            localStorage.setItem('worksheet-user', JSON.stringify(user));\n        }\n\n        function getUsername() {\n            return (document.getElementById('worksheetUsername').value || '').trim();\n        }\n\n        document.getElementById('worksheetUsername').addEventListener('blur', saveUser);\n        document.getElementById('worksheetName').addEventListener('blur', saveUser);\n        document.getElementById('worksheetPeriod').addEventListener('blur', saveUser);\n\n        // ==================== QUESTION IDs & EVENTS ====================\n        function assignQuestionIds() {\n            const blanks = document.querySelectorAll('.blank');\n            blanks.forEach((blank, idx) => {\n                blank.dataset.questionId = `WS-${UNIT_ID}-Q${idx + 1}`;\n            });\n        }\n\n        function addSaveIndicators() {\n            document.querySelectorAll('.question').forEach(q => {\n                if (!q.querySelector('.save-indicator')) {\n                    const indicator = document.createElement('span');\n                    indicator.className = 'save-indicator';\n                    indicator.textContent = '\\u2713 saved';\n                    q.appendChild(indicator);\n                }\n            });\n        }\n\n        function bindBlankEvents() {\n            document.querySelectorAll('.blank').forEach(blank => {\n                blank.addEventListener('blur', () => handleLiveUpdate(blank));\n                blank.addEventListener('keydown', (e) => {\n                    if (e.key === 'Enter') {\n                        e.preventDefault();\n                        handleLiveUpdate(blank);\n                        focusNextBlank(blank);\n                    }\n                });\n            });\n        }\n\n        function focusNextBlank(current) {\n            const blanks = Array.from(document.querySelectorAll('.blank'));\n            const idx = blanks.indexOf(current);\n            if (idx >= 0 && idx < blanks.length - 1) {\n                blanks[idx + 1].focus();\n            }\n        }\n\n        // ==================== ANSWER CHECKING ====================\n        function normalize(str) {\n            return (str || '').toLowerCase().trim().replace(/[^\\w\\s./-]/g, '');\n        }\n\n        function checkAnswer(blank) {\n            const userAnswer = normalize(blank.value);\n            const acceptedRaw = blank.dataset.answer || '';\n            const accepted = acceptedRaw.split('|').map(normalize);\n\n            blank.classList.remove('correct', 'partial', 'incorrect', 'revealed');\n\n            if (!userAnswer) return 'empty';\n\n            if (accepted.includes(userAnswer)) {\n                blank.classList.add('correct');\n                return 'correct';\n            }\n\n            const partialMatch = accepted.some(ans =>\n                userAnswer.includes(ans) || ans.includes(userAnswer)\n            );\n            if (partialMatch) {\n                blank.classList.add('partial');\n                return 'partial';\n            }\n\n            blank.classList.add('incorrect');\n            return 'incorrect';\n        }\n\n        function checkAnswers() {\n            const blanks = document.querySelectorAll('.blank');\n            let correct = 0, partial = 0, total = 0;\n\n            blanks.forEach(blank => {\n                if (blank.value.trim()) {\n                    total++;\n                    const result = checkAnswer(blank);\n                    if (result === 'correct') correct++;\n                    else if (result === 'partial') partial++;\n                }\n            });\n\n            const scoreEl = document.getElementById('scoreDisplay');\n            if (total > 0) {\n                const pct = Math.round((correct / total) * 100);\n                scoreEl.textContent = `Score: ${correct}/${total} (${pct}%)` + (partial > 0 ? ` +${partial} partial` : '');\n                scoreEl.classList.add('visible');\n            } else {\n                scoreEl.classList.remove('visible');\n            }\n\n            pushAllAnswers();\n            refreshDrawerIfOpen();\n        }\n\n        function showAnswers() {\n            document.querySelectorAll('.blank').forEach(blank => {\n                const answers = (blank.dataset.answer || '').split('|');\n                blank.value = answers[0] || '';\n                blank.classList.remove('correct', 'partial', 'incorrect');\n                blank.classList.add('revealed');\n            });\n            document.getElementById('scoreDisplay').classList.remove('visible');\n            pushAllAnswers();\n            refreshDrawerIfOpen();\n        }\n\n        function resetAnswers() {\n            document.querySelectorAll('.blank').forEach(blank => {\n                blank.value = '';\n                blank.classList.remove('correct', 'partial', 'incorrect', 'revealed');\n            });\n            document.querySelectorAll('textarea').forEach(ta => {\n                ta.value = '';\n                ta.classList.remove('graded-E', 'graded-P', 'graded-I');\n            });\n            document.querySelectorAll('.ai-feedback').forEach(fb => fb.remove());\n            document.getElementById('scoreDisplay').classList.remove('visible');\n            gradingState.clear();\n        }\n\n        // ==================== SERVER SYNC ====================\n        function handleLiveUpdate(blank) {\n            const questionId = blank.dataset.questionId;\n            if (!questionId) return;\n\n            const now = Date.now();\n            const lastTime = debounceMap.get(questionId) || 0;\n            if (now - lastTime < DEBOUNCE_MS) return;\n            debounceMap.set(questionId, now);\n\n            sendAnswer(blank);\n        }\n\n        async function sendAnswer(blank) {\n            const username = getUsername();\n            if (!username) return;\n\n            const questionId = blank.dataset.questionId;\n            const answer = blank.value.trim();\n\n            try {\n                if (window.railwayClient && window.railwayClient.submitAnswer) {\n                    await window.railwayClient.submitAnswer(username, questionId, answer);\n                } else {\n                    await fetch(`${window.RAILWAY_SERVER_URL}/api/submit-answer`, {\n                        method: 'POST',\n                        headers: { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' },\n                        body: JSON.stringify({\n                            username,\n                            question_id: questionId,\n                            answer_value: answer,\n                            timestamp: Date.now()\n                        })\n                    });\n                }\n                showSaved(blank);\n                spawnUploadParticle(blank);\n            } catch (err) {\n                console.warn('Failed to sync answer:', err);\n            }\n        }\n\n        function pushAllAnswers() {\n            document.querySelectorAll('.blank').forEach(blank => {\n                if (blank.value.trim()) sendAnswer(blank);\n            });\n        }\n\n        function showSaved(blank) {\n            const question = blank.closest('.question');\n            if (!question) return;\n            const indicator = question.querySelector('.save-indicator');\n            if (indicator) {\n                indicator.classList.add('visible');\n                setTimeout(() => indicator.classList.remove('visible'), 2000);\n            }\n        }\n\n        function spawnUploadParticle(blank) {\n            const particle = document.createElement('span');\n            particle.className = 'upload-particle';\n            particle.textContent = '\\u2191';\n            const rect = blank.getBoundingClientRect();\n            particle.style.left = `${rect.left + rect.width / 2}px`;\n            particle.style.top = `${rect.top - 5}px`;\n            particle.style.position = 'fixed';\n            document.body.appendChild(particle);\n            setTimeout(() => particle.remove(), 900);\n        }\n\n        // ==================== AGGREGATE DRAWER ====================\n        function injectAggregateButtons() {\n            document.querySelectorAll('.question').forEach(q => {\n                const blanks = q.querySelectorAll('.blank');\n                if (blanks.length > 0 && !q.querySelector('.aggregate-trigger')) {\n                    const btn = document.createElement('button');\n                    btn.className = 'aggregate-trigger';\n                    btn.textContent = '\\uD83D\\uDCCA Class';\n                    btn.onclick = () => openDrawerForQuestion(q);\n                    q.appendChild(btn);\n                }\n            });\n        }\n\n        function openDrawerForQuestion(questionEl) {\n            currentQuestionBlanks = Array.from(questionEl.querySelectorAll('.blank'));\n            const drawer = document.getElementById('aggregateDrawer');\n            const content = document.getElementById('drawerContent');\n\n            drawer.classList.add('open');\n            content.innerHTML = '<p>Loading...</p>';\n\n            loadAggregateData();\n        }\n\n        async function loadAggregateData() {\n            const content = document.getElementById('drawerContent');\n            let html = '';\n\n            for (const blank of currentQuestionBlanks) {\n                const questionId = blank.dataset.questionId;\n                if (!questionId) continue;\n\n                try {\n                    const stats = await fetchQuestionStats(questionId);\n                    html += renderBarChart(questionId, stats);\n                } catch (err) {\n                    html += `<p>Error loading ${questionId}</p>`;\n                }\n            }\n\n            content.innerHTML = html || '<p>No data available.</p>';\n            spawnPeerSnow();\n        }\n\n        async function fetchQuestionStats(questionId) {\n            if (window.railwayClient && window.railwayClient.getStats) {\n                return await window.railwayClient.getStats(questionId);\n            }\n            const res = await fetch(`${window.RAILWAY_SERVER_URL}/api/question-stats/${questionId}`);\n            return await res.json();\n        }\n\n        function renderBarChart(questionId, stats) {\n            const responses = stats.responses || stats.distribution || {};\n            const entries = Object.entries(responses).sort((a, b) => b[1] - a[1]);\n            const maxCount = entries.length > 0 ? Math.max(...entries.map(([, c]) => c)) : 0;\n\n            if (entries.length === 0) {\n                return `<div class=\"bar-chart\"><strong>${questionId}</strong><p>No responses yet</p></div>`;\n            }\n\n            let html = `<div class=\"bar-chart\"><strong>${questionId}</strong>`;\n            entries.slice(0, 8).forEach(([answer, count]) => {\n                const widthPct = maxCount > 0 ? (count / maxCount) * 100 : 0;\n                html += `\n                    <div class=\"bar-row\">\n                        <span class=\"bar-label\" title=\"${answer}\">${answer}</span>\n                        <div class=\"bar-container\">\n                            <div class=\"bar-fill\" style=\"width: ${widthPct}%\"></div>\n                        </div>\n                        <span class=\"bar-count\">${count}</span>\n                    </div>\n                `;\n            });\n            html += '</div>';\n            return html;\n        }\n\n        function closeDrawer() {\n            document.getElementById('aggregateDrawer').classList.remove('open');\n            currentQuestionBlanks = [];\n        }\n\n        // Escape key closes drawer\n        document.addEventListener('keydown', (e) => {\n            if (e.key === 'Escape' && document.getElementById('aggregateDrawer').classList.contains('open')) {\n                closeDrawer();\n            }\n        });\n\n        function refreshDrawerIfOpen() {\n            if (document.getElementById('aggregateDrawer').classList.contains('open') && currentQuestionBlanks.length > 0) {\n                loadAggregateData();\n            }\n        }\n\n        function spawnPeerSnow() {\n            for (let i = 0; i < 5; i++) {\n                setTimeout(() => {\n                    const snow = document.createElement('span');\n                    snow.textContent = '\\u2744';\n                    snow.style.cssText = `\n                        position: fixed;\n                        right: ${20 + Math.random() * 300}px;\n                        top: ${100 + Math.random() * 200}px;\n                        font-size: 1.2em;\n                        color: #90caf9;\n                        pointer-events: none;\n                        animation: snowDrift 1.4s ease-out forwards;\n                    `;\n                    document.body.appendChild(snow);\n                    setTimeout(() => snow.remove(), 1400);\n                }, i * 100);\n            }\n        }\n\n        // ==================== AI GRADING ====================\n        async function gradeAllReflections() {\n            const btn = document.querySelector('.btn-ai');\n            btn.disabled = true;\n            btn.textContent = '\\u23F3 Grading...';\n\n            const textareas = ['reflect1', 'reflect2', 'exitTicket'];\n\n            for (const id of textareas) {\n                const textarea = document.getElementById(id);\n                if (!textarea) continue;\n\n                const answer = textarea.value.trim();\n                if (answer.length < 20) {\n                    showFeedback(id, { score: 'I', feedback: 'Please write a more complete response (at least 20 characters).' });\n                    continue;\n                }\n\n                try {\n                    const result = await gradeReflection(id, answer);\n                    gradingState.set(id, {\n                        result,\n                        originalAnswer: answer,\n                        appealCount: 0,\n                        history: []\n                    });\n                    showFeedback(id, result);\n                } catch (err) {\n                    console.error('Grading error:', err);\n                    showFeedback(id, { score: 'I', feedback: 'Error grading response. Please try again.' });\n                }\n            }\n\n            btn.disabled = false;\n            btn.textContent = '\\uD83E\\uDD16 Grade My Reflections';\n        }\n\n        async function gradeReflection(questionId, answer) {\n            if (!window.buildReflectionPromptU5L4) {\n                throw new Error('AI grading prompts not loaded');\n            }\n\n            const prompt = window.buildReflectionPromptU5L4(questionId, answer);\n            const rubric = window.getRubricU5L4(questionId);\n\n            const response = await fetch(`${window.RAILWAY_SERVER_URL}/api/ai/grade`, {\n                method: 'POST',\n                headers: { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' },\n                body: JSON.stringify({\n                    scenario: {\n                        topic: 'AP Statistics - Biased and Unbiased Point Estimates',\n                        questionId,\n                        lessonContext: window.LESSON_CONTEXT_U5L4\n                    },\n                    answers: { answer },\n                    prompt\n                })\n            });\n\n            if (!response.ok) throw new Error('Grading request failed');\n            return await response.json();\n        }\n\n        function showFeedback(questionId, result) {\n            const textarea = document.getElementById(questionId);\n            if (!textarea) return;\n\n            textarea.classList.remove('graded-E', 'graded-P', 'graded-I');\n            textarea.classList.add(`graded-${result.score}`);\n\n            const container = document.getElementById(`${questionId}-feedback`);\n            container.innerHTML = '';\n\n            const feedback = document.createElement('div');\n            feedback.className = 'ai-feedback';\n\n            let html = `\n                <div class=\"ai-feedback-header\">\n                    <span class=\"score-badge score-${result.score}\">${result.score === 'E' ? 'Essentially Correct' : result.score === 'P' ? 'Partially Correct' : 'Incorrect'}</span>\n                </div>\n                <div class=\"ai-feedback-body\">${result.feedback || ''}</div>\n            `;\n\n            if (result.matched && result.matched.length > 0) {\n                html += `<div class=\"ai-feedback-matched\">\\u2713 You addressed: ${result.matched.join(', ')}</div>`;\n            }","numLines":500,"startLine":600,"totalLines":1203}},"sourceToolAssistantUUID":"b7919192-e89b-47c0-ba99-bb5a447cd108"}
